HEADWORD: Ligulated
<hw>Lig"u*la`ted</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧g"⟦usl⟧*l⟦amac⟧`t⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>ligul⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>Ligule</er>, and cf. <er>Lingulate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Like a bandage, or strap; strap-shaped.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Composed of ligules.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ligulate flower</b></col>, <cd>a species of compound
flower, the florets of which have their corollets flat, spreading out
toward the end, with the base only tubular.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ligule</ent>⟦br⟧
